headline.print_headline: How the Dow Jones Industrial Average Did
headline.main: How the Dow Jones Industrial Average Did

lead_paragraph: Stocks closed mostly higher Tuesday as traders got back to work after a long holiday weekend. Health care stocks rose more than the rest of the market after pharmaceutical company Actavis said it was buying rival Forest Laboratories for $25 billion in cash and stock. The Dow was held back by a decline in Coca-Cola, which reported disappointing fourth-quarter results.
